ovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=2764.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3154.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utemplarmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Templarmage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/01 5:09:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Need help - what to get?</span><hr size=1> My name is Oakstaff Farsight, i am a recent graduate of the 24th circle (non-twink), and i am looking for ways to improve my equipment.<br>
I have the following:<br>
2X wis +2 ear <br>
2X wis +2 ring<br>
Electrum jade bracer (+10mana and hp)<br>
Belt of purity<br>
Most of my armor is reinforced (im a tailor)<br>
i do have a Lockjaw Vest<br>
Wpns  Combine scimitar<br>
off hand  Bone Talisman<br>
I m at a lost as to where to go and what to do to get some better items.  After just purchasing my new set of spells, i have about 200pp on me.  But i would prefer working towards obtaining my items rather than being them.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for your help! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujegorah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jegorah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/01 5:22:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help - what to get? - lvl 20 in same boat</span><hr size=1> I am in the same boat.  I'm level 20 and I've been working on the testament of vanear and paw of opolla quests without much luck due to the heavy volume of people camping them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujegorah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jegorah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/01 5:23:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help - what to get?</span><hr size=1> BTW, what is the purity belt?  And what does the combine scimitar do? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utemplarmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Templarmage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/01 5:41:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> more info</span><hr size=1> Jegorah - <br>
<br>
Purity belt is +2str +2wis ac3, sells for like 2pp...<br>
Got one when i went to Ocean of Tears in my long travels...  easy to get.<br>
Combine scimitar, you buy them from Gipsy camp in Oasis for like 42pp and change, it s 5dmg, 24 del and magical.  I upgraded my FS scimitar to this one so i could hit magical creatures!  I also got a Bloodforge Hammer (13dmg/50del +10sv mag) thru the Trumpy quest.  But i find it so slow.....  and i ve got a Runed Totem staff (9dmg, 37del, +5mana or something like that) also pretty slow...<br>
<br>
Anyways, just dont know where to go from here...  i ve seen the equipment lists, etc...  but holy crap, they re pretty long... just looking for guidance... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujegorah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jegorah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/01 10:50:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help - what to get?</span><hr size=1> Well here is my thoughts.  Most of the items can't be had until either you have a ton of platinum or you are level 35+.  For our level the best things to get are the testament of vanear and the paw of opolla.  The testament quest starts at the crow in qeynos.  Give moodro 2gp for the book container, then give him 6 gp UNTIL he gives you a jester card.  Give him the card back and he'll give you one page for the testament.  THe other page is on Dyllin Starshine in highpass hold.  Swim under the inn to a secret smuggler cave.. he is in there every 7 hours or so.  Heavily camped tho.  THe combined book gives 10 wis 10 mana. <br>
<br>
<br>
The paw quest is more lenghty.  It starts in qeynos sewers with Vin Moltar.  Get him a ratear pie (get a baker to make it after getting the recipe from the qeynos hills hermit by giving him 3 giant rat ears) and 3 bottles of khalish.  He'll give you the container.  You have to get 4 rings.. silver in the lake in blackburrow, copper and gold from trading mutant fungus drops from upper guk to lady in erudin, and platinum by camping a mummy that spawns every few hours at teh entrance to befallen.<br>
<br>
Other than that, get some earrings and finger rings off some jewelers.  There are various 3wis hats around, too.  Other than that, most of the wisdom to be had is a bit later. Oh yeah, the ancient croc in upper guk drops gaterskin leggings for 4wis.  No idea where in guk he is though... I'll be heading there myself soon.<br>
<br>
Jegorah<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/utemplarmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Templarmage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/19/01 6:35:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Got the Testament</span><hr size=1> Got the Testament!  Not difficult at all, except i really do hate sitting in one spot for prolonged period of time without doing anything...   i m kinda of turned off the Paw quest for that reason, plus as you pointed out Jegorah, Befallen is often camped by higher lvl...<br>
Any other suggestions out there?<br>
<br>
Oakstaff Farsight <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/urtcll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RtcLL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/19/01 12:10:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> uhh</span><hr size=1> uhh theres no wis on purity belt <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dr00dlfg>dr00dLFG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 10:01:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help - what to get?</span><hr size=1> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/28/01 10:46:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help - what to get?</span><hr size=1> Well...what to get what to get? he he he. lvl up a bit more, then go to sol a and get in a forman group, and hopefully get a formans tunic, and also maybe you will get a charred guardian sheild (10ac 9wis). The biggest suggestion I have is first getting the testament like others have said, and lvl! Don't really worry about your stuff for a while, and suddenly without knowing it you will have some nice items or pp to get better stuff. Other than a testament and a Runed Falchion (very good friend), your stuff is about like mine at that lvl. Now at 40 I have 202wis with some nice stuff (earned all of it myself) and 2.5k in the bank :). Also...learn to become a master of EC, one good way to make some extra cash is if you see a good deal, snatch it up, then even it may take a bit, have some patiace and you can make a profit :)(got a BCP for 300pp back when they were still like 2k...sold it for 1.8k...things like that :) ).<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=2764.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3154.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=2930.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=2930.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2930.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2930.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Gu